cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, and specifically on video segmentation for autonomous robots. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a modification to the convLSTM cells, which is related to the architecture of neural networks and could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The application of the proposed method to autonomous robots suggests a connection to cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on different datasets, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
